#### **Paso 2: Conectar Android con Backend (1 hora)**
Crear `ApiService.kt`:
```kotlin
interface ApiService {
    @GET("dictionary")
    suspend fun getSigns(
        @Query("search") search: String? = null,
        @Query("category") category: String? = null
    ): List<SignResponse>
    
    @GET("dictionary/{word}")
    suspend fun getSignDetail(@Path("word") word: String): SignDetailResponse
    
    @GET("modules")
    suspend fun getModules(): List<ModuleResponse>
}
```

Crear `RetrofitInstance.kt`:
```kotlin
object RetrofitInstance {
    private const val BASE_URL = "http://10.0.2.2:8000/" // Emulator accede asÃ­ a localhost
    
    val api: ApiService by lazy {
        Retrofit.Builder()
            .baseUrl(BASE_URL)
            .addConverterFactory(GsonConverterFactory.create())
            .build()
            .create(ApiService::class.java)
    }
}
```

Actualizar `DictionaryScreen.kt` para usar datos reales:
```kotlin
LaunchedEffect(Unit) {
    viewModelScope.launch {
        try {
            val response = RetrofitInstance.api.getSigns()
            signs = response
        } catch(e: Exception) {
            // Manejar error
        }
    }
}
```

